    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured party assisted to boat landing",
      "Transport via Motor Vessel Mr. Mag to HI A376 A for medical evaluation",
      "Field medic provided first aid",
      "Helicopter transport to HI A595 CF for physician consultation",
      "Helicopter transport to PHI base in Cameron, LA",
      "Ambulance transport to South Cameron Memorial Hospital"
    ],
    "summary": "On 12-June-2015 at 12:30 hours, a contract crane mechanic placed a 5-foot pry bar (approximately 18 pounds) in a vertical position against a handrail at the base of the East Crane Gantry while gathering tools to depart due to inclement weather. The pry bar slid over and fell approximately 25 feet through the handrail, striking a contract operator on the hard hat. The impact caused a severe laceration to the scalp (6-7 inches in length) and resulted in a Lost Time Accident exceeding 3 days requiring medical evacuation.",
